# Main Execution Sequence Diagram
#
# Shows the high-level flow of command execution from user request
# through the CLI adapter and the 8-step commandsvc.Service.Execute pipeline.
#
# Source: cmd/invowk/app.go (CLI adapter), internal/app/commandsvc/service.go (Service.Execute)

vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: tala
  }
}

title: |md
  ## Main Execution Sequence
|

shape: sequence_diagram

# Participants
User
CLI: CLI Adapter (cmd/invowk/)
SVC: Command Service (commandsvc/)
Config: Configuration
Disc: Discovery Engine
CUE: CUE Parser
Registry: Runtime Registry
Runtime: Selected Runtime

# Entry point
User -> CLI: "invowk cmd <name> [args...]"
CLI -> SVC: "Execute(ctx, request)"

# Step 1: discoverCommand
SVC -> Config: Load configuration
Config -> CUE: Parse config.cue
CUE -> Config: Config struct
Config -> SVC: Configuration loaded
SVC -> Disc: "discoverCommand(ctx, req)"
Disc -> CUE: Parse invowkfile.cue files
CUE -> Disc: Invowkfile structs
Disc -> CUE: Parse *.invowkmod directories
CUE -> Disc: Module structs
Disc -> SVC: "CommandInfo + Diagnostics"

# Step 2: resolveDefinitions
SVC -> SVC: "resolveDefinitions(req, cmd)\nMerge flag/arg defaults"

# Step 3: validateInputs
SVC -> SVC: "validateInputs(req, cmd, defs)\nCheck flags, args, platform"

# Step 4: resolveRuntime
SVC -> SVC: "resolveRuntime(req, cmd, cfg)\n3-tier: CLI flag > config > command default"

# Step 5: ensureSSHIfNeeded
SVC -> SVC: "ensureSSHIfNeeded(ctx, req, resolved)\nStart SSH server if container + host access"

# Step 6: buildExecContext
SVC -> SVC: "buildExecContext(req, cmd, defs, resolved)\nProject env vars (INVOWK_FLAG_*, INVOWK_ARG_*)"

# Dry-run intercept (between buildExecContext and dispatchExecution)
SVC -> CLI: "If --ivk-dry-run: return dry-run data"
CLI -> CLI: "Render dry-run plan → exit 0\n(skips dispatchExecution entirely)"

# Step 7: dispatchExecution
SVC -> Registry: "createRuntimeRegistry(cfg)"
Registry -> SVC: "Registry + Cleanup"
SVC -> Registry: "Get(runtimeMode)"
Registry -> SVC: Runtime instance
SVC -> Runtime: Execute(context)
Runtime -> Runtime: Run script/command
Runtime -> SVC: Result

# Return result
SVC -> CLI: "Result + Diagnostics"
CLI -> CLI: "renderAndWrapServiceError()\nApply lipgloss styling"
CLI -> User: Output + Exit code

# Watch mode (when --ivk-watch, wraps entire pipeline)
CLI -> CLI: "watchLoop (--ivk-watch)\nWait for file changes → debounce → re-execute\nInfra errors abort after 3 failures\nCtrl+C to stop"
